erican guitarist (d. 2006)\n*  1936   &ndash; [[Shelley Morrison]], American actress (d. 2019)\n*  1936   &ndash; [[Gy\u00f6rgy Pauk]], Hungarian violinist and educator\n*  1936   &ndash; [[Etelka Ken\u00e9z Heka]], Hungarian writer, poet and singer\n*[[1940]] &ndash; [[Eddie Henderson (musician)|Eddie Henderson]], American trumpet player and educator\n*  1940   &ndash; [[John Horgan (academic)|John Horgan]], Irish academic and politician\n*[[1941]] &ndash; [[Steven Kellogg]], American author and illustrator\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Charlie Landsborough]], English singer-songwriter and guitarist\n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Bob Hoskins]], English actor, singer, and director (d. 2014)\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Milton Nascimento]], Brazilian singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*  1942   &ndash; [[Zdenko Runji\u0107]], Croatian songwriter and producer (d. 2004)\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Jonathan Williams (racing driver)|Jonathan Williams]], English race car driver and pilot (d. 2014)\n*[[1944]] &ndash; [[Jim McCann (musician)|Jim McCann]], Irish singer and guitarist (d. 2015)\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Pat Conroy]], American author (d. 2016)\n*  1945   &ndash; [[Demetris Th. Gotsis]], Greek poet and author\n*  1945   &ndash; [[Nancy Davis Griffeth]], American computer scientist and academic\n*  1945   &ndash; [[Jaclyn Smith]], American actress and producer\n*[[1946]] &ndash; [[Kevin Barron]], English electrician and politician\n*  1946   &ndash; [[Keith Hopwood]], English singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer \n*  1946   &ndash; [[Pat Sajak]], American journalist, actor, and game show host \n*  1946   &ndash; [[Holly Woodlawn]], Puerto Rican actress and author (d. 2015)\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Ricardo Asch]], Argentinian gynecologist and endocrinologist\n*  1947   &ndash; [[Ian Ashley]], German-English race car driver\n*  1947   &ndash; [[Hillary Clinton]], American lawyer and politician, 67th [[List of Secretaries of State of the United States|United States Secretary of State]] and 44th [[List o